snippet: Less than two weeks after a vote to elect an assembly, hopes of renewed momentum to create a constitution were dampened after the violent attack.
abstract: Dozens of armed rioters storm Parliament in Tripoli, Libya, setting fire to grounds and injuring lawmaker in expression of anger at slow transition of power following ouster of Col Muammar el-Qaddafi; incident dampens hopes of renewed momentum for transition or even break from violence.

byline.contributor: Suliman Ali Zway contributed reporting from Benghazi, Libya, and Osama al-Fitori from Tripoli.

lead_paragraph: Less than two weeks after a vote to elect an assembly, hopes of renewed momentum to create a constitution were dampened after the violent attack.

headline.main: Frustrated With the Pace of Change, Rioters Storm Parliament Building in Libya
headline.print_headline: Frustrated With the Pace of Change, Rioters Storm Parliament Building in Libya
